My sister's on my case about how it's "self destructive" to hang out with friends who like to cuddle and all that jazz. She thinks I'm going to be led into the "orgy lifestyle," and that I'm going to be sexually promiscuous because I was leaning on Lawrence during a movie.

She's furious with me for disagreeing and says I'm immature for not seeing it. She's "older and wiser," she tells me. She may be older and know more about life, but she knows jack all about spirituality.

She's bitter and she criticizes everybody. I mean she's such a closed-minded individual...I mean I am happy she told me how she felt, but did she have to attack me? No, she did not.

from the time your eyes looked into mine
my face was frozen still in time
every day you gaze at me
you fill me with your ecstasy
as you work me to the core
i tug your hair and beg for more
addicted to your touch i sigh
as your hand moves up my thigh
i need you here, i need you now
you've opened up my rock somehow
your jaws of life are ectsasy
through my jeans they climb my tree
slowly with your teeth you pull
as metal passes metal full
your tongue it drives me wild so loose
my legs they spread so fine obtuse
as you lead me into fire
i tense up quick, this wild desire
with that i make my final moan
the tension drops, loose to the bone

I really want to read the book Jane Eyre. I am certain that it would be quite intellectually stimulating. So anyway I hung out with Geoff and later, I will be going to Detour with Miranda with the skimpy shirt she lent me money to buy. When I get home after seeing “Zazu,” I will study Linguistics for a bit, and then perhaps panic over Calculus and go over the text book items. And I cannot wait for Madonna’s next album. It will be produced by Stuart Price (Zootwoman, X-Static Process) and Mirwais (Music, American Life) She has also reportedly gotten the London Community Gospel Choir (Nothing Fails) and Bloodshy (Toxic, AM to PM) to produce her next record. She is apparently throwing a lot of balls up in the air. Along with Bloodshy's reported dance-thumper and the choir and electronic sounds, the album will have a slight trip-hop and rocked-up feel to it. A latin track will also be included, according to reports. It seems like her album, much like Bedtime Stories, will be a mix of many different sounds, like electronica, rock, trip hop, gospel, disco, latin and hip hop. The current title is Project 05, as a working title. I simply cannot wait for this!

A repeat of three poems. You have already seen these. But I had to post something tonight, so this is what I posted! Got a problem with it? Hearts that Bleed Hearts that bleed Eyes that rain A rock hard place, Isolated in the desert of ice I don a black cape I move in for the kill, The rock hard place entombed in my mind I jump the cliff, My wings that soar, Gently gliding in the sacred sky The Beautiful Stranger He's standing there, So unaware that he is being watched Just walking now, gracefully down the hallway Part of me hopes that he is aware of my watchful gaze, Another part, however, is horrified As I sit, I vow to one day meet this young gentleman With whom I shared a city bus with every Monday and Wednesday For about six months I can't say yet if I will bed this beautiful stranger But I must admit I do long for his boyish eyes To look back at mine To stare back deeply, if not for a moment, for an eternity Only not from a distance as I do unto him But up close, where each and every breath can be felt On the surface of our cheeks Or breathing down my neck As my body turns away from his His hands slowly but softly roaming my torso and stomach As he explores, he gets lower and lower As his fingers dip below my belt And I close my eyes, lift my head and exhale Where will this go? I cannot say, I'll leave it up to fate The Lone Eye Here I sit on this soft felt chair My eyes fixated on the cold ice screen The light staring right back at me With no hint of acknowledgement of my existance Waiting...I sit Waiting...I breathe I call out a name, but alas...nobody is there to hear me Second by second, minute by minute, hour by hour My eyes burning into the depths of the endless screen Burning deeper, where there is no end No fear, no dream No sign of life for light years ahead Staring endlessly through the night Frozen and locked through time and space

<font size="-3">I’m a bit shaken, but I’ll be alright.  I suppose.

I don’t know.  I guess I am just a bit hurt by recent events, but the only person I really can blame it on is myself.  Maybe I hurt too easily.  I dunno...I don’t know what to think because I get upset way too damn much for the stupidest reasons.  Maybe this is why I’m not popular.  Not that I’d ever want to be, anyway.

People I guess think that...I think before I speak, and the truth is, I don’t.  Maybe I’m just too sensitive and I need to be a bit tougher, the way I like to think I used to be at one point.

I guess too much is changing at a rapid pace, but really I don’t know sometimes you know?  It’s true, I’m not as innocent as I’d like to think I am, but I’m not a monster either. 

I don’t know.  I’m too shaken to analyze it any further.  I’ve got to go to bed, for I have school. Goodnight.

Things should be better now anyway.
</font>

THE UNTAMED WATER an evening sky peppered with specks of glistening light woven through an unreachable dark blanket by the bruised and calloused fingers of an elderly woman, dressed in blacks and dark grays. she sighs heavily as the night air pushes through the grass, trees and cold, trickling streams there is nothing but fury and pain in her eyes empty of tears that will one day return from the depths of the seas and the deep, deep oceans. she is a vengeful soul, without a merciful strand on her treacherous head of long flowing hair the untamed water is her dear friend, responding to her every whim and desire rising venomously high with an intent to kill, she cackles dryly revelling in her revenge. the elderly woman has had the last laugh

“Those who only give, will receive. Those who only take, will be miserable beyond tolerance.” I really wish I had my own recording studio so that I could produce my own music. Record my own sounds, etc. I’d be in there all the time as a hobby, creating sounds, playing with them, making mixes to my favorite songs. I’ve been busy writing for my new poetry set. “Guilty Pleasure” is the name of the one poem I am currently working on. Of course, there’s also fotolog, which I have been neglecting, but I’ve been too busy jotting down notes, going around town with my notebook for photo shoot ideas. And I have lots of songs to redownload. Lindsay Lohan’s “Rumors,” Mozart’s 40th, and more!

Gosh some people are just mean mean mean, and they don't even give a shit. It's this self-centered-ness that causes so much controversy and drama. Whatever. I just gotta remind myself that I'm above being rude to people when they haven't done anything wrong. If I'm having a bad day, it's not like I treat everyone else terribly. I may vent but that's it. I CHALLENGE any ONE of you to remind me of a time I personally attacked you due to my mood, without being provoked. Yes, like any human being I may WANT to just strangle someone, anyone, while in a bad mood, but I usually keep it in me, 90% of the time, because I know that in my right mind I would never treat that one person badly. Well I'm done. I don't take that kind of bullshit from anyone. Ima start usin' the blocker, because I don't deserve this. Life is about the world, past, present, future, and people as a whole. Life isn't just about you. Every thing we do affects others, and it's about time we fucking LEARN that it's NOT GOOD to treat someone like a third class citizen for no good reason other than "I had a bad day. So fucking deal with it." I mean if you don't feel like talking, why are you on MSN anyway if you're so pissy? Anyway, *hugs* to whomever is reading this. Not many people even read my entries much anymore anyway.

And I can't wait for it to come at the end of the week! It's much cooler than my last one. I mean it's nothing special, but if you've seen my current one you'd know how much of a difference it is. Here's a picture: http://www.shoprogers.com/store/wireless/products/phones/products_details.asp?shopperID=Jorabi&PRODUCTID=X426&summary=1 And here's another poem, “Mind-Trapper.” MIND-TRAPPER i've crossed the line, there's no turning back must think of my assets, not of what i lack the cloth has been cut, the door is unlocked a great pulling force of those whom are mocked insatiable desire, an effortless plane a selfish endeavor stepping onto the train freedom awaits, like the wine-stained sky entrapment contained, i may finally fly but this is a risk of a broken wing to give me my story, and a song to sing i struggle to find my navigational map with this i shall fall, a treacherous trap

<font size="-3">You wanted a list? You got it!
There are so many anti-Theresa lists of crimes out there, I figured that it was about time to make one for Gwen. What do you think? Not that Theresa is innocent. But they give Gwen too much credit! I've done it before, but I think this is more thourough...

Ok, well this isn't a list of "crimes," but it shows Gwen's true character.


Constantly pressuring Ethan into proposing when she knew that he needed time to adjust to Harmony.


Having a hissy fit every time she saw Ethan and Theresa together, even if it was misconstrued. If the situation were reversed, Theresa would have run out crying. Gwen would have attacked them and murdered them. Funny.


Interrogated Theresa about her alleged "boyfriend" at Theresa's father's funeral!


Glared at Theresa at midnight when Theresa's "father" died falling through the skylight just because she ran into Ethan's arms. So Ethan's arms are more important than a father. I see. 


Fussing because she thinks someone has a "crush" on Ethan. Whether or not she was right, or whether or not Theresa was scheming, that is definite insecurity.


Threatening to leave Ethan because he couldn't give her an engagement ring (then Theresa took it off and let Ethan propose to Gwen). People say Theresa tried to sell Ethan out to a tabloid and that she purposely kept the ring. TRUE about the ring, but at least minute she decided to do what was right. Same with the tabloid thing. 


Told Ethan that he could keep Theresa as his mistress so long as Gwen can become "Mrs. Ethan Crane" (I only heard that from several sites...I didn't see that episode and I don't even know if it is true)


Tried to seduce Ethan after he called off the wedding, by following her mother's plan of using sexy lingere. And when she used the glass of water to feign phony tears? I don't think Rebecca had anything to do with that.


Even though she didn't want Theresa to walk in on them, Gwen used the moment to gloat to Theresa that she was in bed with Ethan.


Attacked Theresa (or at least tried to) with a baseball bat and tried to strangle her. (And "Payback's a Bitch" isn't a good excuse in my opinion...Adults, especially ones of high society with reputations, should consider that they are held responsible for their actions)


Locked Pilar in a closet in an attempt to murder her daughter.


Eavesdropped on Tabitha so that she could accuse Theresa of being a witch (the tealeave thing)


Schemed with her mother to sabatoge Ethan and Theresa's only real date.


Lying about how she doesn't care about the Crane money.


When Theresa gave back the engagement ring and ran off, Gwen manipulated Ethan into thinking Theresa was a golddigger. She made him think that Theresa left Ethan because she couldn't have the diamond ring anymore. He believed it. Ethan believed Theresa didn't love him anymore because he was no longer a Crane. She showed up. With her life savings. For Ethan. Ethan realized that Theresa didn't run out of the mansion because she didn't keep the ring. But so that she could give her life savings to help Ethan get back on her feet. Something Gwen wouldn't have done in those days.


Gloating about how she would "rule society" when she had "more power than Ivy" as Mrs. Ethan Crane (before she learned of Theresa's betrayel...she wasn't sweet turned evil. She was selfish through and through. Her and Theresa should be a couple. They would work.)


Gloated whenever possible. Still does. Not as much. Weird.


She got her and Ethan's friends Robert and Sharon to sneak in conversation of Gwen and Ethan's memories so that Ethan would forget about Theresa (does this count??)


Used her "best friend's" death as a tool to get close to a grieving Ethan.


Used this death to manipulate Ethan into thinking that Theresa didn't give a hoot about him (just after saying that Theresa was obsessed with him. weird)


Destroyed a gift Theresa gave to Ethan...a very significant teddy bear.


Gwen's racist. She called Theresa "Teresita" in a mocking manner. She made a stupid "sombrero" joke in the Bermuda elevator. She yelled "mija" when she raised the bat over Theresa's head. With her mother, (not lately though...) calls Theresa a Chalupa. But she never called Theresa a taco queen. Why would she say Chalup..never mind!!!


Later used it to frame Ethan for hating Theresa by telling her that Ethan ripped it up and threw it in the trash (or down the stairs)


Vowed to her mother to do anything in her power to falsley make Theresa look as bad as possible in front of Ethan.


Schemed with Mommy Dear to expose Ethan's relationship with Theresa to Luis.


Helped distract Ivy so that her mother could get the proof she needed to destroy Ethan.


Tricked Ethan into kissing her (with a "last goodbye kiss") Ay! That sounds like something Psycho Theresa would do!


Plotted and schemed with her mother to destroy lives by sending an e-mail containing a shocking secret to a tabloid. Traitors. Don't say that they didn't want to destroy lives. Gwen specifically say "I will destroy Theresa." And Rebecca specifically said "We will bring down the house of Crane" and Gwen smiled with a snicker.


Lied to Ethan and Theresa about being over Ethan.


Plotting with her mother to become Mrs. Ethan Crane by having him adopted. (For the same reasons as Theresa...Gwen wanted to give Ethan back his life so that it wouldn't be in shambles, and become a Crane. Wow)


Planning an engagement party (much like Theresa planning a wedding) for the sole purpose of using it to destroy her rival.


Lied to Theresa, telling her that now that Ethan isn't a Crane, he will never love her again.


Used a voice distorter on more than one occasion to tip the tabloid off with the false information about Theresa being the one who sold Ethan out (when it was her and her wench of a mother). Rebecca even had to cut the cord (pull it out of the wall actually) because Gwen was going too far and Rebecca said she needed to be patient.


Helped her mother send a copy of the tabloid to Ivy's room.


Delayed the wedding as much as possible by yelling out when Father Lonigan said "If anyone shall object..." Okay, that's not a crime lol. Never mind! Okay, then I will say something else...um...yes. Stalked Theresa with her mother by following Ethan and Theresa to Bermuda (what business did Gwen have with Ethan to follow him to Bermuda??)


Lied to Ethan, saying she was sorry. Okay, maybe she did feel bad about what she did, but she turned right around to gloat, right after saying that she "realizes" that Theresa isn't a "bad person" just someone who makes "mistakes." Ha! Gag me.


Clinging to Ethan the second he breaks up with Theresa so that she is there to pick up the pieces.


After all Theresa's been through (hell and back literally, getting the man she wanted and then losing him after waking up married to his ex-father and pregnant with the baby, "executed," thrown herself down an elevator shaft, was accused of something Rebecca [and Gwen] did), Gwen hasn't been through all that. She is too independant (now anyways), and yet when Ethan chose Gwen because of her baby, Gwen gloated like crazy!


Reprimanded her mother for manipulating Luis and Sheridan when she was doing the exact same thing with Ethan and Theresa.


Lied to Theresa, claiming she never lied to get Ethan's love. Ha!


Lied again, saying that when Ethan and Theresa were together, she stepped back and let them have their happiness.


Speaking ill of the dead when Ethan says he is sad about Theresa's alleged death, and Gwen said that Theresa was a bitch who didn't deserve anybody crying over her death.


Being furious that Theresa had "come back to life."


Let's not forget how rude Gwen is and arrogant. "Housekeeper's daughter." And holy camole, burn! She totally burned Hank when he asked her out.


Walked out on Father Lonigan after he said what she was planning to do was evil.

Scoffed when an angel warned her that her evil deeds would bring evil to Harmony. 


Adding to the pressure at the double wedding by constantly adding snide remarks about how Theresa did this and that. On her wedding day. Not the night before. The day of.


Plotting to destroy the wedding of her best friend! (Not for that purpose, but that's beside the point). Oh yeah, that is actually good because she saved Sheridan's life. Go figure.


Tried to drug Theresa's tea. (Ha! And Theresa switched cups. LMFAO)


Uses her baby every time she can to make Ethan focus on her. (I can't say that I blame her for that one though)


Reprimands Theresa's scheming face when she is just as bad if not worse


Being compassionate for the sake of looking good in front of Ethan (Not too sure 'bout that one)


Again, gloating that "the end of Theresa" is coming.


Plotting to become Mrs. Crane by insisting Ethan and her stay in the mansion (which they have no right to live because Gwen's mother is Julian's puta.)


When Theresa was going to make love to Ethan, Gwen broke into the Lopez-Fitzgerald home (again) and started to interrogate Theresa. When Theresa was naked. In bed. I think.


Talk about classy. Moaning extra loud in bed as a means of gloating. (it's true. Oh Ethan! with her snicker and her pupils looking to Theresa's door. And the hickey? That was so dumb.


Lying about Ivy, saying Ivy would never manipulate, when clearly she knows Ivy's manipulative nature. She just wants Theresa to look bad in insulting Ethan's mother.


Constantly breaking (or trying to break) commandments. Stealing. Attempted murder (actually with murderous intent!). Parental dishonour. 


Attacking Theresa at the hospital, then trying to make it look like Theresa wanted to stress her out as a means to murder her baby.


Ignoring the doctor's wishes, not caring that her baby could die, so she could go play hanky panky with Ethan at the Crane apartment.


Once again ignoring doctor's ORDERS by choosing to choke Theresa over the life of her own baby.


Blaming Theresa for losing her baby, when she is to blame as well.


Schemed with her mother to get revenge on Theresa and make her lose her son.


Schemed with her mother to make Theresa's entire family lose their jobs.


Schemed with her mother to make the Lopez-Fitzgeralds homeless.


Had the Lopez-Fitzgeralds evicted from their home so that they could take Little Ethan.


Had the Lopez-Fitzgeralds blacklisted all over town.


Tried to force Theresa to murder the implanted baby.


Strangled Theresa in court.


Threw Theresa out of a window.


Attacked Theresa with a bedpan.


Stabbed Theresa with a scalpel, leaving her paralyzed.


Trying to choke Sheridan to death.


Attacking her mother.


Slitting her wrists in a murderous plot.


Chasing Theresa around the hospital with a pair of scissors.


Kidnapping Theresa's baby.



I'm sure there's more. I just can't think of them right now. And it's NOT like Terrorcita sites where they repeat the same one again and again to make the number of misdeeds larger. Like this: Theresa disrespects her mother. Another one will say "Theresa disobeyes Luis and her mother." Then one will say "Theresa acted against her family." Then one will say "She broke the ten commandments." Then one will say "She tried to kill, steal, covet, all wrong according to the Bible." The one will say "She made love to Ethan against Pilar's wishes." Then one will say "She made love to Ethan before their wedding." Then one will say "She disobeyed her brother's wishes for her about premarital sex." Come on!

I think she's psycho. Would a sane person (no matter what) go to someone's house with a baseball bat, lock a middle-aged woman in a closet with murderous intentions, stab mannequins (however u spell it), and frame people for ridiculous things???

“Zazu” and I went with Alyssa to Chinook Mall to play “DDR.” Unfortunately, there were many people there, and both “Zazu” and I only got to play two songs. Oh yes, and we bumped into Daniel, and I met a whole bunch of new people that were hanging out there, Maddy, Aydree, Orry, and many others. I so wanted Lawrence there. I miss him! I was so upset that I couldn’t contact him, and when he found out, so was he. *frowns* “Zazu” and I went to have some sushi, and then she helped me with my Kabbalah string. Afterwards, I headed to the French Maid’s “Speakeasy.” I went with Syd and Angela. Today, I went with my sister Natalie to get Japanese food, and later I’m going clubbing with her. Good stuff.

I would totally say something because I have so much to say, but I can’t because I don’t know what to say. The best friend I ever had is more distant to me now than ever before, my other best friend is also kind of estranged from me...we’re drifting... But through it all, just at the right time, two of my other really good friends made me feel a whole lot better. I’m sorry if this entry seems a bit too sappy. Wait a minute, no, I’m not sorry. Why should I be sorry for how I feel? If you find it “cheesey,” well then GOOD. Dairy’s good for you anyway. This is General Cristofski signing off, in a trance, unsure of what emotion he’s feeling. It must be fate.

I have been nominated for Poet of the Year 2004 for my Mind-Trapper poem “Hearts That Bleed,” by Poetry.com and The International Association of Poetry! Of course, this isn’t anything “huge,” but it’s still cool! In addition to being published in two books and a poetry CD, I also won the December 2004 Editor’s Choice award, which led to the nomination. Just cool stuff.

Ever get the feeling that you just don’t have any friends? “At the moment?” Or you do, but when you’re busy, they are always available...and when you really need to talk to somebody, or just hang with somebody, nobody is anywhere to be found? I'm supposed to see Frank today, but I’m afraid I wont be able to because I’m going to be running very late. Just one of those days, that’s all. Just one of those days. I just don’t want to be alone tonight, that’s all. I guess I deserve it after some of the things I’ve done to other people throughout my life. Karma’s a bitch isn’t it? Whatever...I know I’ll have a happier day sometime soon...my days are never really consistant, which I guess in a way is good. It’s just that, while I’ve never really had any friends until about three years ago, its funny how now, I feel more alone than ever. It’s like an illusion...we just always feel alone. And once we don’t feel that way anymore, we feel smothered. But I know fate will step in somewhere down the road. And I’m going to find my life.

A poem is worth a thousand pictures... Here it is, my brand-new poetry collection, for anybody who is bored enough and has the time to read it! It’s my honest work, and very personal. I do hope any poetry-lovers will enjoy this. Of course, this will probably be ignored because nobody I know is a crazy poetry-fanatic, lol, but oh well. I still said what I had to say, whether or not people are listening. MIND-TRAPPER THE UNTAMED WATER an evening sky peppered with specks of glistening light woven through an unreachable dark blanket by the bruised and calloused fingers of an elderly woman, dressed in blacks and dark grays. she sighs heavily as the night air pushes through the grass, trees and cold, trickling streams there is nothing but fury and pain in her eyes empty of tears that will one day return from the depths of the seas and the deep, deep oceans. she is a vengeful soul, without a merciful strand on her treacherous head of long flowing hair the untamed water is her dear friend, responding to her every whim and desire rising venomously high with an intent to kill, she cackles dryly revelling in her revenge. as many lives are lost, the elderly woman has had the last laugh HEARTS THAT BLEED WINNER OF POETRY.COM'S EDITOR'S CHOICE AWARD DECEMBER 2004 Hearts that bleed Eyes that rain A rock hard place, Isolated in the desert of ice I don a black cape I move in for the kill, The rock hard place entombed in my mind I jump the cliff, My wings that soar, Gently gliding in the sacred sky MY EJECTOR it's a state of confusion like this love profusion running through my head everything that i dread unsure of where to go so that i may grow head is thrusting like fusion it's a hasty conclusion all those pictures you painted left my body so tainted what was simple and light shining strikingly bright forbidden desires lighting my fires like jeans, memories faded i've never been so jaded red stained pieces, broken glass skeletal invasion, etched into my mass skull is bleeding, no light up ahead my soul is retreating like an old waterbed i'm feeling suddenly torn all my thoughts so forlorn spinning out of control symbols burning my soul calling children of fate my heart must abate my patience is worn my ejector is born MIND-TRAPPER i've crossed the line, there's no turning back must think of my assets, not of what i lack the cloth has been cut, the door is unlocked a great pulling force of those whom are mocked insatiable desire, an effortless plane a selfish endeavor stepping onto the train freedom awaits, like the wine-stained sky entrapment contained, i may finally fly but this is a risk of a broken wing to give me my story, and a song to sing i struggle to find my navigational map with this i shall fall, a treacherous trap THE BEAUTIFUL STRANGER He's standing there, So unaware that he is being watched Just walking now, gracefully down the hallway Part of me hopes that he is aware of my watchful gaze, Another part, however, is horrified As I sit, I vow to one day meet this young gentleman With whom I shared a city bus with every Monday and Wednesday For about six months I can't say yet if I will bed this beautiful stranger But I must admit I do long for his boyish eyes To look back at mine To stare back deeply, if not for a moment, for an eternity Only not from a distance as I do unto him But up close, where each and every breath can be felt On the surface of our cheeks Or breathing down my neck As my body turns away from his His hands slowly but softly roaming my torso and stomach As he explores, he gets lower and lower As his fingers dip below my belt And I close my eyes, lift my head and exhale Where will this go? I cannot say, I'll leave it up to fate SOCIAL DISEASE Thought I was on my way Had a plan Had a dream What shallow things must I do? I think I've caught your social disease You confused me You used me I got a social disease What must I do to prove to you Some of it was my fault too? Now I'm confused Don't know what to think I wish I could undo all I did to you Don't want no social disease For my world is shaken Hopes shattered, dreams scattered I'm so confused I'm so ashamed I wish I could see things more clearly But I can't...I've got your social disease DAMAGE CONTROL this is what i want i've wanted it for a very, very long time my heart aching for it every night as i went to sleep my life based on a simple desire but is this what i really want? i'm just living out my dream and i just realized that i was misled this is the direction i've brought my life, and i've got to save myself before i make myself cry it's easy to sit back and watch it all be torn down but i've got to calm it down if i want to save a life FRUSTRATION sitting alone in complete frustration back to the wall in deep meditation eyes are closed in contemplation on whether i believe in church damnation don't know what is false, don't know what is fact don't know what to think, don't know how to act wish i had the answers, wish i had a way wish i knew the difference, night and day love is powerful, love is song love is neither right nor wrong OUT OF THAT LIFE Sitting at a bus stop bench Pondering life and my state He was not a father to me Nothing that he wouldn't do to be able to be one So much warning came A spot to be replaced Emptiness left unfilled Couldn't let him see me cry Don't know what he'd see right now It's not like I know what I'm doing anyway Now there's this other man Dressed in bright rainbow colors effortlessly Heart is dark and empty Looks like he lost someone too Could I be that filler? Can I fill that space? Is there a reason I was brought into this time and place? There's still another man What do I hope to gain, Except heartache and pain? My heart belongs to myself It belongs to no one else Put up a wall and shut it all out of here But my belief remains Shouldn't matter who you choose to love Why must I cry so hopelessly? Fate will bring me closer So don't you ever tell me to stop One must express it all A victim of a kind of rage How much could it hurt? Don't even know which road to take Maybe I'm still empty too Maybe that's why I'm still here THE LONE EYE Here I sit on this soft felt chair My eyes fixated on the cold ice screen The light staring right back at me With no hint of acknowledgement of my existance Waiting...I sit Waiting...I breathe I call out a name, but alas...nobody is there to hear me Second by second, minute by minute, hour by hour My eyes burning into the depths of the endless screen Burning deeper, where there is no end No fear, no dream No sign of life for light years ahead Staring endlessly through the night Frozen and locked through time and space THE ANTI-MERCY i am trapped here now how will i escape? i'm falling like bricks my head is splitting my heart is slipping don't know which one to follow and which one to ignore can't follow my heart into a vastly harsh doom i'm in a cage with a fork in the road the hard metal banging against my forehead cannot eat, cannot sleep cannot laugh, cry, or speak fine lines between anger and hate i'm shaken, i'm lost i need to find my tree my head is spinning out of control in total confusion, like my heart proceeding so cautiously not knowing what to do i'm tainted i'm no longer virginal white now ripped into colors of darkness aloof i lower my head and pray for mercy
